Hi everyone & guten Tag!

I help forward-thinking tech brands *increase* their positive impact and *grow* their bottom line through the power of STORY. :muscle:

I'm a German-American brand communications practitioner with 20 years of experience on European and North American markets. I have lived and worked in Los Angeles, Toronto, Düsseldorf & Stuttgart in Germany. I just moved to Montreal, Canada, and I'm looking for a remote opportunity in a strategic content / communications role.

I'm also happy to support you and contribute my expertise and experience. Thanks for having me here! :pray:

Hiya!

I’m a B2B content marketer for a company called Moveworks, and I’m all about storytelling … _especially_ if you have a technically complex product. Currently, I’m based in the SF Bay Area, but I’ve lived and worked in the Russian Far East, as well as a couple of other far-flung locales.

Looking for fellow marketers working at fast-growing companies who’re trying to keep up during this “unprecedented time.” Let me know if there’s anything I can help with, because I know I’ll be asking for help myself :slightly_smiling_face: Btw… my company is always hiring :writing_hand:

text:
:woman-raising-hand:Hi everyone! So excited to have found this community and to be honest, I don't even remember how I ended up here... but I'm glad I did!

:writing_hand:I'm a freelance writer in Toronto :flag-ca:. I just started doing some writing with a SaaS content agency and I'm also working on some web copy projects. I also do a lot of personal essay writing, for various publications, and recently have been using Substack as a way to express the thoughts that don't necessarily fit anywhere else.

Personally, I'm married and have two boys (5 and 2.5), and they give me a lot to write about. They also give me huge bags under my eyes.

:point_down:Here are my links... look forward to connecting and learning!

:bird: <https://twitter.com/steph_rebecca|https://twitter.com/steph_rebecca>
:link:<https://stephaniegilman.com|https://stephaniegilman.com>
:newspaper: <https://thankyouforsharing.substack.com|https://thankyouforsharing.substack.com>
:woman:<https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephanie-gilman/|https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephanie-gilman/>

attachments.text: The latest Tweets from Stephanie Gilman (@steph_rebecca). Writer. Over-thinker. Previous breast cancer-haver. Mom of two boys who hate sleep. Subscribe to my newsletter for the good stuff :point_down: #binders (she/her). Toronto

Hi Everyone!
I am so excited to have found this community, :heart_eyes: I actually went on Google and searched the keywords "best slack channels to be in" and Viola!! Here I am. Magical!!:slightly_smiling_face: 

I'm a storyteller in Lagos, Nigeria; currently studying Products and finding new interesting ways to tell products stories.

Mt foundation is in Media so I also have a few produced films and a lot of unproduced Screenplays :smiley:. I have also had my fair share of experience in TV and Radio as a visual storyteller.

I am open for networking, connecting, learning and contributing to this community.

 I wish us the best of luck as we sail together :heart:
